  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Nan et al. [54] argue that diversity should be considered in addition to similarity.",
    "As the context length is limited, organizing all the example information (i.e., NL question, schema, SQL) into the prompt ensures the quality of examples but sometimes may exceed the context length.",
    "DAIL-SQL [41] proposes a method that balances the quality and token quantity by removing examples' schemas, which are token-cost.",
    "Role-playLLMs can be assigned roles when prompting them.",
    "For instance, Zhao et al. [96] test a prompt like \"Suppose you are an expert in statistical analysis\"."
  ],
